<p>Last week I joined <a href="https://www.val.town/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">val.town</a> as <a href="https://stevekrouse.com/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">Steve Krouse</a>’s cofounder. Val.town is a system for programming in the small, for writing short programs in TypeScript that can link together into something larger. It’s for writing that scheduled web scraper or basic API that you wanted to make but didn’t want to add to your pile of servers on AWS or GCP. It’s already a lot of fun to use, and is going to keep getting better.</p>

